  "prompt": "What is the reason of non immune hydrops in foetus?",
  "response": "Non-immune hydrops fetalis (NIHF) is a serious condition characterized by abnormal fluid accumulation in two or more fetal compartments. There are several potential causes of non-immune hydrops:\n\n1. Cardiovascular causes:\n- Congenital heart defects\n- Arrhythmias\n- Structural heart abnormalities\n\n2. Chromosomal/Genetic disorders:\n- Turner syndrome\n- Trisomy 13, 18, 21\n- Multiple genetic syndromes\n\n3. Hematologic disorders:\n- Alpha-thalassemia\n- Hemoglobinopathies\n- Severe anemia\n- Bone marrow failure\n\n4. Infectious causes:\n- Parvovirus B19\n- Cytomegalovirus\n- Toxoplasmosis\n- Syphilis\n\n5. Metabolic disorders:\n- Gaucher disease\n- Hurler syndrome\n- Other lysosomal storage diseases\n\n6. Pulmonary/Respiratory causes:\n- Congenital pulmonary airway malformation\n- Lung hypoplasia\n\n7. Fetal tumors:\n- Sacrococcygeal teratoma\n- Neuroblastoma\n\n8. Placental causes:\n- Twin-to-twin transfusion syndrome\n- Placental chorioangioma\n\n9. Miscellaneous:\n- Fetal hydrops\n- Chylothorax\n- Idiopathic causes\n\nComprehensive evaluation is crucial to determine the underlying cause.",
